Large flock of AMGO visiting Tulip Poplar that has my feeders. I was leaning against the back of the house ca 12 m away from tree but birds did not go to feeder while I was there.  Instead, they remained among the branches of the tree. Number of birds varied as birds came and when but was always about 30-40, minimum. Segments interrupted by approaching car. Final segment interrupted by heat pump switching on.
